1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
Ever wonder why we only see one side of the Moon?

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:05,600
It's not hiding.

3
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:11,200
The Moon is tidally locked, spinning in perfect sync with its orbit around Earth.

4
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:19,200
This means it takes the same time to rotate once as it does to orbit Earth — about 27.3 days.

5
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:25,200
So, while it may seem like the Moon's playing coy, it's just how physics works!

6
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:30,000
This tidal locking creates phases, making our Moon's appearance change over time.

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,800
Want to learn more cool science facts?

